expression = re.compile(rfc._DOMAIN_AV_REGEX)
good_examples = ['Domain=a', 'Domain=a-7', 'Domain=foo-77.a-7.aa',
    'Domain=localhost', 'Domain=foo.bar.com', 'Domain=0.0.0.0',
    'Domain=127.0.0.1', 'Domain=250.250.250.250', 'Domain=255.255.255.255',
    'Domain=249.249.249.249', 'Domain=200.200.200.200',
    'Domain=199.199.199.199', 'Domain=100.100.100.100',
    'Domain=2001:0db8:0000:0000:0000:ff00:0042:8329',
    'Domain=2001:db8:0:0:0:ff00:42:8329', 'Domain=2001:db8::ff00:42:8329',
    'Domain=0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:0000:0001', 'Domain=::1']
for good_example in good_examples:
    self.assertTrue(bool(expression.fullmatch(good_example)), msg=
        "Good Domain AV '{m}' not matched by regex".format(m=good_example))
